<db:para>This example opens a window and has a <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtwebsockets-websocketserver.xml">WebSocketServer</db:link> listening for incoming connections and a WebSocket connecting to the <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtwebsockets-websocketserver.xml">WebSocketServer</db:link>. Every time the window is clicked, the WebSocket sends a message to the <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtwebsockets-websocketserver.xml">WebSocketServer</db:link>. The <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtwebsockets-websocketserver.xml">WebSocketServer</db:link> has a signal handler that logs the incoming message to the window and sends a message back again, and the WebSocket has a signal handler that logs the returned message to the window.</db:para>
